# Next.js Patterns

## App Router

- Use `src/app/` for routes — each route is a directory with `page.tsx`
- Default to Server Components. Only add `'use client'` when state, effects, or browser APIs are needed.
- Use `layout.tsx` for shared layouts, `loading.tsx` for suspense, `error.tsx` for error boundaries

## Imports

- Use `@/` alias for all project imports (maps to `src/`)
- Use `@/components/ui/` for shadcn components
- Use `@/lib/` for utilities and shared logic

## Components

- Place shared components in `src/components/`
- Place route-specific components alongside their route
- Use shadcn/ui primitives over custom implementations when available

## Data Fetching

- Fetch data in Server Components using `async` functions
- Use Server Actions for mutations
- Avoid `useEffect` for data fetching
